        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2021-11-15 13:23:44.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Patch Set 1:\n> \n> > Patch Set 1:\n> > \n> > > Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n> > > \n> > > Hi. I know this is unrelated but what is this:\n> > > \"Using generated security password: 96497452-1ea5-4b06-a34e-4b96467f0b4b\" ?\n> > > \n> > > What is security password used for? Why is it generated in the container not within helm chart? Why it is outputed to logs?\n> > \n> > Hi Krzysztof. Can I ask you where you are seeing this? I cannot see it in the logs of the Jenkins Jobs. Perhaps I missed it?\n> \n> https://logs.onap.org/onap-integration/gating//125680-1/k8s/k8s/kubernetes-status/pod-onap-policy-clamp-cl-pf-ppnt-b58fb6775-7f2ff-policy-clamp-cl-pf-ppnt-logs.html\n\nAh yes, I see. This happens because including the spring-boot-starter-security dependency in your Spring Boot project will cause it to auto-generate the password if it is not specified in the application.properties or application.yaml. It will randomly generate a password and print it to the logs. This password is not actually used in the application at all. There is a fix on the way through got this also here: https://gerrit.onap.org/r/c/policy/clamp/+/125610 and here: https://gerrit.nordix.org/c/onap/oom/+/11285",
        "patchset_number": 1
